title: Renée Slegers - Wikipedia
snippet: Renée Josiena Anna Slegers (Dutch: [rəˈneː joːˈsinaː ˈʔɑnaː ˈsleːɣərs]; born 5 February 1989) is a Dutch football coach and former player, who is the head coach of Women's Super League club Arsenal.

title: Renée Sleger's Net Worth, Ethnicity, Partner and Personal Life
snippet: Renée Slegers was born on February 5, 1989, in Someren-Eind, a small town in the Netherlands’ Noord-Brabant province. Her ethnicity is Dutch, rooted in the cultural and historical context of the Netherlands.

title: Renée Slegers appointed head coach | News | Arsenal.com
snippet: Born in the Netherlands, Renée originally joined us as assistant coach in the summer of 2023, following a two-year spell in charge of Rosengard, where she won back-to-back Swedish league titles in 2021 and 2022.
